To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
\frac{4}{5}\div\frac{9}{20}
=\frac{4}{5}\times\frac{20}{9}
=\frac{4\cdot 20}{5\cdot 9}
=\frac{80}{45}
\]

Now simplify by dividing numerator and denominator by 5:

\[
\frac{80}{45}=\frac{16}{9}.
\]

So the simplified result is \(\displaystyle \frac{16}{9}\) (or as a mixed number, \(1\tfrac{7}{9}\)).
